        "left":{
            "body":"When Wisconsin achieved statehood in 1848, one of its first major political acts was to establish the University of Wisconsin, the Madison campus of which directly faces the <a class='network-link' href='#/action/intro'>Capitol</a>.",
            "caption":"<b>Right:</b> Lincoln statue in front of Bascom Hall, UW-Madison."
